    "assistantText": "I’m not able to run the web search reliably right now, so I can’t pull fresh, specific MSP/SI leads with verified email addresses for you.\n\nGiven your constraints (need emails, MSPs/SIs, relaxed size and geography), doing this well really depends on being able to search and open individual company “Contact” pages in real time. Without that, anything I list would be guesswork and at high risk of being wrong or out of date.\n\nIf you want to proceed manually, here’s the most reliable, low-friction way to get to your 20 leads with emails:\n\n1. Search patterns to use\n   - Google/Bing queries:\n     - `“managed IT services” “North Carolina” “contact us”`\n     - `“IT managed services” “Ohio” “contact”`\n     - `“MSP” “Cleveland” “managed IT”`\n     - `“IT support services” “Raleigh NC”`\n     - To find emails directly:\n       - `“managed IT services” “@gmail.com”` (sometimes very small MSPs use generic emails)\n       - `“managed IT services” “info@” “contact”`\n\n2. How to qualify quickly\n   For each result:\n   - Confirm they are an MSP or IT services/SI:\n     - Look for “Managed IT Services,” “IT Support,” “Cloud Services,” “Network Management,” “Systems Integration,” etc.\n   - Approximate size (relaxed, so just rough):\n     - Check LinkedIn company page (number of employees).\n     - If no LinkedIn: small, regional client list, owner’s mobile number on site, or local-only focus usually implies <~200 employees.\n   - Geography:\n     - Prioritize NC and OH, but if you can’t reach 20, expand to neighboring states (SC, GA, PA, MI, IN, KY, VA, TN).\n\n3. Extract the details you need\n   For each qualified company, capture:\n   - Company name\n   - Website\n   - City, State\n   - Services keywords (Managed IT / SI / Cloud / Security)\n   - Email (ideally from “Contact” or “About” page)\n   - Optional: phone, LinkedIn URL\n\n   Typical email locations:\n   - Footer of any page\n   - “Contact,” “Support,” “Help Desk,” or “Get in Touch” pages\n   - “About Us” or “Our Team” pages\n   - Sometimes in the privacy policy or terms pages\n\n4. Sample structure you can paste into a sheet\n   Use these columns:\n\n   - Company Name  \n   - Website  \n   - City  \n   - State  \n   - Type (MSP / SI / IT Services)  \n   - Est. Size (e.g., 10–50, 51–200, 201–500)  \n   - Contact Email  \n   - Phone  \n   - Notes (e.g., “strong MSP focus; offers cloud & security”)\n\n5. If you want, I can:\n   - Help you refine search strings for specific cities in NC/OH you care about (e.g., “Charlotte, Raleigh, Greensboro, Durham, Cincinnati, Columbus, Cleveland, Dayton, Toledo”).\n   - Draft an outreach email template optimized for these small MSP/SI targets.\n   - Help you quickly qualify a list you’ve already started (you paste companies; I help you decide which fit MSP/SI criteria and how to categorize them).\n\nOnce search access is stable again, I can directly fetch and validate 20+ leads under your relaxed constraints (looser size and geography, but strict on having an email)."
